            {
                "name": "Always",
                "url": "/topics/always"
            },
            {
                "name": "Given",
                "url": "/topics/given"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527797",
        "quote": "More and more I think of privatisation as being not just about the takeover of resources and power by corporate interests, but as the retreat of citizens to private life and private space, screened from solidarity with strangers and increasingly afraid or even unable to imagine acting in public.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527797"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Private",
                "url": "/topics/private"
            },
            {
                "name": "Increasingly",
                "url": "/topics/increasingly"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527779",
        "quote": "Men explain things to me, still. And no man has ever apologized for explaining, wrongly, things that I know and they don't. Not yet, but according to the actuarial tables, I may have another fortysomething years to live, more or less, so it could happen. Though I'm not holding my breath.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527779"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Explain",
                "url": "/topics/explain"
            },
            {
                "name": "Another",
                "url": "/topics/another"
            },
            {
                "name": "According",
                "url": "/topics/according"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527782",
        "quote": "The great majority of people are calm, resourceful, altruistic or even beyond altruistic, as they risk themselves for others. We improvise the conditions of survival beautifully.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527782"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Survival",
                "url": "/topics/survival"
            },
            {
                "name": "Great Majority",
                "url": "/topics/great_majority"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527784",
        "quote": "I feel often that we don't have the right language to talk about emotions in disasters. Everyone is on edge, of course, but it also pulls people away from a lot of trivial anxieties and past and future concerns and gratuitous preoccupations that we have, and refocuses us in a very intense way.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527784"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Away",
                "url": "/topics/away"
            },
            {
                "name": "Very",
                "url": "/topics/very"
            },
            {
                "name": "Gratuitous",
                "url": "/topics/gratuitous"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527787",
        "quote": "Panic is rare, looting is essentially insignificant, people are not terrified and trampling each other to flee from a disaster scene, but in fact are trying to manage a situation. We may in fact revert to some sort of primordial civility.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527787"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Fact",
                "url": "/topics/fact"
            },
            {
                "name": "Some",
                "url": "/topics/some"
            },
            {
                "name": "Other",
                "url": "/topics/other"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527788",
        "quote": "To say that everything without exception is going straight to hell is not an alternative vision but only an inversion of the mainstream's 'everything's fine.'",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527788"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Going",
                "url": "/topics/going"
            },
            {
                "name": "Exception",
                "url": "/topics/exception"
            },
            {
                "name": "Mainstream",
                "url": "/topics/mainstream"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527791",
        "quote": "We are entering an era of heightened disaster, thanks to climate change. Being prepared for disaster will mean being prepared to sift truth from rumour, and being prepared to adjust our worldview.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527791"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Change",
                "url": "/topics/change"
            },
            {
                "name": "Prepared",
                "url": "/topics/prepared"
            },
            {
                "name": "Will",
                "url": "/topics/will"
            }
        ]
    },
    {
        "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527795",
        "quote": "Sometimes it seems that the fate of the world is decided entirely in the ether of electronic communications and corporate backroom deals.",
        "author": {
            "name": "Rebecca Solnit",
            "url": "/quotes/rebecca_solnit_527795"
        },
        "topics": [
            {
                "name": "Decided",
                "url": "/topics/decided"
            },
            {
